description: This is a supporting document for the RDF Dataset Canonicalization specification, providing some extra explanation of the problem space and associated use cases.
title: RDF Dataset Canonicalization and Hash Working Group — Explainer and Use Cases

versions.title: RDF Dataset Canonicalization and Hash Working Group — Explainer and Use Cases

description: RDF [RDF11-CONCEPTS] describes a graph-based data model for making claims about the world and provides the foundation for reasoning upon that graph of information. At times, it becomes necessary to compare the differences between sets of graphs, digitally sign them, or generate short identifiers for graphs via hashing algorithms. This document outlines an algorithm for normalizing RDF datasets such that these operations can be performed.
title: RDF Dataset Canonicalization
